= LAMMPS Scaling Tests =



[wiki:doc/CbenchDocumentation Back to Cbench Documentation]

== Rhodo.scaled runtime scaling ==

[[Image(runtime_rhodo_scaling.png)]]

||'''Steps''' || '''Real Time (min)'''  || '''CPU Loop Time (min)'''||
||100    || 18.99      || 17.99        ||
||200    || 34.45      || 33.76        ||
||300    || 52.46      || 51.79        ||
||500    || 88.39      || 87.67        ||
||1000   || 185.4      || 184.72       ||


 * Runtime scales linearly with the number of steps specified in the input deck file
 * Runtime can also be scaled by increasing problem size, if desired
